district on east beiruts northern flank was more optimistic 
weto make it he said i dont think the world 
is going to al the annihilation of 1 million christians thisng to stop 
lahhoud said he and his neighbors while away the hours in 
running games of poker and backgamloor 
underground shelter which houses a power generator 
the citys moslem sector is virtually a ghost town tens of 
thousands of residents have fled to relative safety in east and 
south lebanon 
those who stayed behind also spend nights in shelters as 
soldiers with multibarreled mobile rocket launchers roam around 
firing off a barrage then moving quickly before retaliatory fire 
comes civilians take the punishment 
