a dead rat might not be worth a rats 
whisker in lapeer county soon or even the 10cent bounty allowed 
by an obscure state law 
the 1915 law provides the bounty to anyone who kills a rat and 
turns it over in a state of good preservation to their 
municipal clerk the clerk is to burn the rats head and authorize 
payment through the county 
but the law also allows county boards of commissioners to 
rescind the bounty a move that lapeer county clerk mary ellen 
thick said in a recent interview that she would welcome 
im sure they have not done that but well be doing that 
soon she said itll be presented to the board of 
commissioners immediately 
the bounty law surfaced recently during the celebration of 
marathon townships 150th anniversary of incorporation 
township clerk laura ring recalled receiving an anonymous letter 
in 1985 from a resident who said he had killed 76 rats and wanted 
to know whether he had to cut off their heads before receiving his 
760 bounty 
i went to the board meeting wearing surgical gloves that 
month ring said i actually had visions of a sack of rats 
