the final result of an election to the west coast before the final 
votes are counted rep james h quillen rtenn told the house 
the only critic of the bill to take the floor rep william 
frenzel rminn described it as a rube goldberg device that 
will louse up the states cause them a great deal of confusion and 
travail 
he said it actually could reduce turnout by shortening voting 
hours on the west coast and possibly prompting east coast states to 
open the polls at later hours than they do now 
rep al swift dwash the measures sponsor said studies have 
shown an earlier poll closing will prompt voters to vote earlier 
and thus the fear of a drop in turnout is simply not 
substantiated by the facts 
