<TEXT>
psychologists are consulting with 
nationally recognized experts on disasters and tragedies to help 
residents young and old cope with the nations worst oil spill 
the stress down there in valdez is incredible said tom 
scott director of the southern region emergency medical services 
council 
people need to be aware the stress is going to be affecting 
them they need to be aware that their stress is going to impact on 
their children 
a 24hour tollfree telephone line staffed by mental health 
professionals to take calls from the distressed is being set up 
scott said wednesday the national aeronautics and space 
administration set up a similar line for its employees in the 
aftermath of the space shuttle challenger disaster 
among the most common feelings are hopelessness helplessness 
and worthlessness he said 
scott has been consulting with jeffrey mitchell a psychologist 
at the univerity of marylandbaltimore county known to police fire 
and medical services around the country as the founder of a process 
known as critical incident stress debriefing 
the process is designed to relieve the stress emergency service 
personnel encounter in masscasualty incidents and other crises 
a variation of the process may be valuable to the prince william 
sound communities devastated by the spill scott said 
mitchell has done similar work in other afflicted communities 
like palm bay fla after a gunman shot up a shopping mall 
killing six people and wounding 10 
mitchell warned that the children in the valdez area would be 
among the first to show the stress 
he said dont be surprised if children ask for cooking oil to 
put in the bathtub or out in the mud puddle scott said 
kansas psychologist richard gist a leading disaster expert was 
scheduled to arrive in valdez today said mark johnson state 
coordinator of emergency services 
mental health professionals should plan on seeing problems 
for two to three years at least scott said probably 
longer because of the total loss of lifestyle that may occur the 
loss of lifestyle is as important as loss of income 
mitchell suggested to scott that the effects on employment be 
evaluated as quickly as possible those that will lose their 
livelihood for the next year or two will need vocational 
rehablitation or it soon will have a negative impact on their 
mental health scott said 
in the interim scott said the emphasis will be on education 
trying to describe the reactions that are normal in such a 
situation and offering ways to deal with them 
