for cooperating with the united states to fight drug trafficking 
the military exercises agreement was approved by a 1322 vote on 
wednesday the lawmakers who voted no said the measure could hurt 
regional peace efforts 
the two countries have engaged in more than 80 joint military 
training exercises involving at least 60000 us and 20000 
honduran troops during the past 38 years 
the exercises were stepped up in 1982 when relations between 
honduras and the leftist sandinista government in nicaragua 
deteriorated and the united states built an air base in honduras 
honduras also has served as a refuge training ground and 
staging base for nicaraguan rebels about 11000 of whom have lived 
with their families in camps near the nicaraguan border since the 
us government cut off military aid to them in february 1988 
an estimated 1100 american troops currently are stationed at 
the enrique soto cano us air force base about 50 miles northeast 
of tegucigalpa 
the base is considered among the most important centers of us 
military operations in central america washington has been 
supporting the government of el salvador in its nineyear war 
against leftist rebels 
under the drug agreement honduran officials said they will work 
with the united states to crack down on drug production and 
trafficking both nations are to share information and human and 
technological resources 
during the past six years honduras caribbean coast has become 
a transfer point for drug shipments from colombia to the united 
states 
in the mostpublicized local case reputed drug baron juan ramon 
matta returned home to honduras in 1986 after escaping from a 
colombian prison 
his arrest in april 1988 at his home in tegucigalpa and rapid 
deportation to the united states touched off riots extradition of 
hondurans is prohibited by the constitution 
matta remains jailed at the federal prison in marion ill 
serving a threeyear sentence for escaping from a florida prison in 
1971 
</TEXT>
