breakthrough and said it could lead to further flexibility toward 
the mainland 
he said it was probably intended to pressure the chinese 
communists to accept de facto nationalist rule over this island 
the nationalists continue to claim they are the legitimate 
government of all china and have maintained a policy of no 
contacts no talks no compromise toward communist china since 
their defeat on the china mainland 
but in the past year the nationalists have relaxed their policy 
on private contacts between taiwanese and mainland chinese and have 
allowed an exchange of visits trade and cultural ties 
the asian development bank was founded in 1966 to help regional 
development the 47member organization voted in 1986 to admit 
china and changed taiwans membership name from the republic of 
china the official nationalist name to taipei china 
nationalist officials protested then saying the change 
relegated taiwan to a provincial government under china the 
nationalists boycotted the development banks annual meetings in 
1986 and 1987 but attended last years meeting in manila the 
philippines where the bank has its headquarters 
chen said the nationalists are still opposed to the taipei 
china designation he said the nationalists would continue to 
negotiate with the bank to work out a compromise solution 
acceptable to both parties 
since the 1970s taiwan has been virtually isolated 
diplomatically it is now recognized by only 23 nations while most 
other countries recognize the mainland government 
