ranging from about 190 million bushels to as much as 315 million 
bushels this year compared with 323 million bushels produced in 
1988 and a 198688 annual average of 342 million 
kansas wheat farmers planted 124 million acres last fall up 
sharply from 102 million planted for the 1988 crop 
according to one set of jottings abandonment because of dry 
weather might reduce this years harvest to 105 million acres in 
which case yields could average 30 bushels per acre a total state 
output of 315 million bushels 
under another scenario however the kansas crop might be 
reduced to 99 million harvested acres a yield of 25 bushels and a 
total output of 250 million bushels the worst case version calls 
for 93 million acres harvested an average of 20 bushels per acre 
and a total harvest of 190 million bushels 
