was essential to import contract laborers to avoid inflation and 
falling economic competitiveness 
hong kong needs about 50000 imported workers most of them 
unskilled to help fill an estimated 200000 job vacancies it said 
the groups chairman martin barrow an executive at jardine 
matheson holdings ltd said there was danger hong kong could lose 
it competitiveness in the manufacturing sector the hotel 
industry and elsewhere because of the shortage of workers 
the government said tuesday it is considering easing 
restrictions on employment of foreign laborers under current 
policy only foreign workers with skills not available locally are 
allowed to work in the colony 
hong kongs low unemployment rate currently 13 percent is 
considered a key factor behind the economys growth slowing to an 
expected 6 percent this year less than half the 1987 rate 
the labor shortage is due to tight immigration laws and a steady 
drain of talent as the colony approaches its return to chinese 
sovereignty in 1997 
the report said the government should encourage automation and 
productivity through tax breaks and reducing red tape it said 
bringing in workers on sixmonth to twoyear contracts similar to 
practices in singapore would provide relief 
