until now vietnam veterans who came 
here to be treated for posttraumatic stress disorder were likely 
to encounter another kind of stress figuring out how to pay for 
living expenses during their sevenweek stay 
thats about to change 
the midrio grande chapter of the american red cross has been 
awarded more than 100000 to help veterans and their families from 
new mexico arizona and parts of texas pay rent and food costs 
while they are treated at an outpatient clinic at the veterans 
administration medical center here 
