<TEXT>
the senate told it is a guardian of 
tradition without becoming a barrier to change celebrated its 
first two centuries of history on thursday recalling its faltering 
beginnings and noting its many milestones 
april 6 1789 was the date that the first senate meeting in 
new york city finally reached a quorum and thus was able to 
start conducting business after a frustrating month of failing to 
do so 
history oozes from these walls said sen john glenn 
dohio as the day of commemoration began in the old senate chamber 
in the capitol with the issuing of a postage stamp displaying the 
gilt shield and eagle still suspended over the presiding officers 
chair 
the eagle and shield were there during speeches on the old 
chambers floor which served the senate from 1810 to 1859 and can 
be seen in 19th century prints involving three famous senators of 
the era daniel webster of massachusetts henry clay of kentucky 
and john c calhoun of south carolina 
those three senators and the roles they played in the period 
before the civil war were invoked repeatedly as past and former 
senators hailed the senate as an institution 
howard h baker jr of tennessee a former senate republican 
leader said the sense of history in the old senate hall and in 
the senates present chamber first occupied in 1859 is so strong 
that at times one can truly smell the marble 
nearly 20 former senators including baker and former 
democratic leader mike mansfield of montana joined senators in 
the current 101st congress for the ceremonies members of the house 
of representatives celebrated the quorum bicentennial session of 
that body on tuesday 
former sen thomas f eagleton a democrat from missouri said 
that the legacy of the early senate is the art of the american 
political compromise 
today compromise is woven into constitutional fabric of the 
nation eagleton said 
although many senators past and present have regarded compromise 
as morally wrong eagleton said it is politically essential 
compromise in my judgment is getting a bad rap eagleton 
said without it we screech to a halt paralyzed by 
intransigence 
the senate session began at 11 am the hour of the first 
session two centuries ago 
with the conclusion of the ceremonys first half in the old 
chamber senators formed a procession to the senates present 
meeting place down the hall 
senior senators from the states answered the roll call 
beginning with delaware which became the first state in 1787 and 
continuing to hawaii which in 1959 became the 50th to join the 
union 
