of the senate as a stage and recalled some of the drama the 
present chamber has witnessed including the onevote defeat of the 
attempt to oust president andrew johnson during reconstruction 
after the civil war and the rejection of president woodrow 
wilsons effort to bring the united states into the league of 
nations after world war i 
senate majority leader george mitchell dmaine said that while 
the senate has undergone many changes over the years it remains a 
place where the rights of the minority are protected and speech can 
remain virtually unlimited 
it is a guardian of tradition without becoming a barrier to 
change he said 
senators moved in and out of the ceremonies to spirited john 
philip sousa marches played by the marine corps band 
a tourist asked a doorman does a band play every day the 
senate meets 
no the doorman replied only once every 200 years 
