<TEXT>
the united states and italy on thursday signed 
an agreement calling for increased cooperation in the fight against 
terrorism drug trafficking and organized crime 
attorney general dick thornburgh signing the classified 
document at fbi headquarters said the two countries had adopted 
ambitious proposals for combating crimes and terrorism 
our agreement expresses in unmistakable terms the strength of 
our partnership and the vigor of our commitment he said in brief 
remarks 
the agreement was worked out by two groups of american and 
italian experts over three days of talks this week the experts 
have been meeting regularly over the last five years to improve 
cooperation between the two countries 
italian interior minister antonio gava said both sides had 
agreed they would have to be on a war footing in the fight 
against the international cancer of drugs organized crime and 
terrorism 
the projects undertaken by the two nations in their agreement 
include cooperation on extradition on increasing the exchange of 
information about terrorist activities on money laundering by drug 
traffickers and on upgrading enforcement of racketeering laws 
said an italian source he spoke on condition of anonymity 
specifics of the agreement were not divulged 
gava addressing the experts earlier said organized crime 
groups in italy and the united states have been increasing their 
cooperation in recent years 
