peoples organization and 24 members of the south africanled 
security forces have been killed since gunbattles broke out 
saturday when a ceasefire was supposed to take effect 
angolas state news agency quoted swapo defense spokesman peter 
muehihange as saying only 38 guerrillas died in that time and nine 
are missing he said 20 security force members were killed 
foreign minister pik botha of south africa said his government 
is committed to the plan to grant independence to namibia which 
pretoria has ruled for 74 years 
south africa claims swapo has sent more than 1500 guerrillas 
into namibia in violation of an accord requiring the insurgents to 
remain at their bases in angola at least 100 miles away 
the south african council of churches led by prominent 
antiapartheid clergymen said the carnage of the last few days 
could have been prevented if the united nations had denied south 
africas request to let its forces leave their bases to combat the 
guerrillas 
it said the credibility of the un peacekeeping force was in 
doubt 
a joint south africancubanangolan commission monitoring the 
independence accord scheduled a meeting saturday to discuss the 
crisis south africas president pw botha said us and soviet 
observers would participate 
i trust that the commission will be able to find a peaceful 
solution to the very serious situation which has arisen he told 
parliament in cape town 
chester a crocker the assistant secretary of state for african 
affairs left washington on thursday to attend the commission 
meeting 
a namibian police official chief inspector derek brune 
reported more skirmishes thursday across the 300mile front near 
the angolan border he said the guerrillas have broken up into 
small groups and that some fighters were reported as far as 120 
miles south of the border 
cedric thornberry secondincommand of the un contingent 
said the united nations hoped to have its first infantry battalions 
in the battle areas early next week 
the united nations has authorized 4650 troops for the namibia 
operation but only 921 have arrived the only forces in the battle 
area are about 300 logistical personnel 
the united nations accepted a us offer to fly 850 finnish 
soldiers to namibia francois giuliani spokesman for 
secretarygeneral javier perez de cuellar told reporters the men 
could be arriving over the weekend 
swapo officials said the guerrilla fighters had been inside 
namibia for some time and had no intention of leaving or accepting 
a surrender proposal 
but thornberry said it was made clear beyond a shadow of a 
doubt to swapo that it would have to negotiate an additional 
element to the un plan if it wanted bases inside namibia 
the way for namibian independence was cleared in december when 
south africa angola and cuba signed an accord calling for 
withdrawal of 50000 cuban troops who have helped marxist angola 
battle usbacked rebels 
besides granting namibia independence south africa is to end 
military aid to the angolan rebels 
swapo which has been waging a war for independence for 23 
years is favored to win elections scheduled in november under the 
un plan 
