<TEXT>
un human rights officials said thursday 
the soviet union has agreed to sign an accord allowing its citizens 
to take human rights complaints directly to international 
investigators 
they said the soviets would sign the optional protocol to the 
international covenant on civil and political rights 
soviet acceptance of the document would be an extension of 
president mikhail s gorbachevs declaration in december that human 
rights should be given new emphasis in international affairs 
rajsoomer lallah of mauritius chairman of the human rights 
committee associated with the united nations and fausto pocar of 
italy of the committee told reporters the notice was unofficial and 
the soviets had not said when they would sign the protocol 
pocar said he received the assurances during a workshop at the 
center for human rights organized in moscow in november 
lallah said he also had received unofficial confirmation and 
added in october we are going to examine the third periodic 
human rights report of the ussr and it is possible that by 
then the decision will have been taken or in process of being 
taken 
a month ago the soviet union said it would accept world court 
jurisdiction in cases based on the covenant on civil and political 
rights and five other human rights treaties the decision reversed 
a long policy of resisting outside judgment of its practices 
the international covenant on civil and political rights 
guarantees the individuals right to life freedom from torture 
inhuman or degrading treatment freedom from slavery or forced 
labor freedom from arbitrary arrest or detention freedom of 
movement freedom of thought conscience and peaceful assembly and 
free association 
us officials praised last months soviet policy change but 
noted that only governments not individuals can file legal 
actions with the world court whose formal title is the 
international court of justice 
pieter kooijmans un special investigator on human rights 
said at the time it would be a real breakthrough for human 
rights if the soviet union would recognize the right of 
individuals to file complaints of rights abuses 
under the optional protocol individual citizens can complain of 
rights abuses to the human rights committee an international body 
of legal experts with the power to order compensation 
hungary ratified the protocol last year joining 40 other 
nations that recognize it 
</TEXT>
