leftist rebels attacked two 
major military bases in a nationwide offensive thursday and asked 
the rightwing victors in el salvadors presidential election to 
declare themselves a transition government 
the rebel farabundo marti national liberation front said its 
drive came in response to a surge in repression following the 
victory by the republican national alliance or arena in march 19 
elections a communique from the rebel general command accused 
arena of sponsoring the repression 
in a proposal issued separately in mexico city the rebels asked 
the incoming arena government for broad talks embracing government 
rebels the military and all political parties it said arena 
should declare itself a transitional government until new elections 
can be held 
