officials said wednesday they 
broke up a major international counterfeit ring confiscating 12 
million in counterfeit us currency and arresting a west german 
and an israeli accomplice 
the counterfeiters had operated since at least 1987 and their 
bogus money has turned up in several european cities and in africa 
said jochen schroers spokesman for the frankfurt prosecutors 
office 
schroers said investigators seized 235 pounds of counterfeit 
us 100 bills with a total face value of 12 million 
he said it was the largest seizure of counterfeit money in west 
german history 
printing machines and highquality paper used by the 
counterfeiters were also confiscated in raids march 20 in frankfurt 
and the surrounding area schroers said 
two of the counterfeit rings alleged organizers a 49yearold 
israeli and a 43yearold west german businessman from the 
frankfurt area were arrested and an arrest warrant was issued 
for a third suspect schroers said 
the spokesman refused to provide further information on any of 
the suspects 
according to schroers west german authorities received their 
first clues about the counterfeiters in 1987 when they heard the 
ring wanted to circulate a large amount of their bogus money 
we knew no more than that until late summer 1988 when the 
first hundred or so hundreddollar bills surfaced in various 
european cities especially east europe but also in africa 
schroers said 
he said that american and israeli authorities provided 
information about links between the counterfeitiers operating in 
west germany with another ring that was active in 1983 and 1984 
schroers said equipment used by the earlier group had come from 
frankfurt 
according to schroers a member of the earlier ring who is now 
in jail in austria gave authorities information that led to the 
arrest of the israeli man suspected of involvement in the new ring 
of counterfeiters 
west german police confiscated the printing equipment paper and 
counterfeit bills in raids on two residences and a business in the 
frankfurt area schroers said 
