<TEXT>
it was the car cool baby boomers grooved on 
the mustang ford motor cos breakthrough into lightweight 
affordable sports cars turns 25 this month with an immortalized 
place in auto history making its mark the same way the beatles 
reshaped rocknroll 
teenagers dreamed of cruising driveins in their new mustangs 
which like the dreamers themselves grow older by the year some 
original mustang drivers say they dont feel a day older than when 
they slid behind the wheel for the first time 
it felt great stanley tucker of montreal remembered about 
the day 25 years ago when he drove the first mustang ever made at 
fords dearborn mich assembly plant where 52 of the cars an 
hour still roll off the line 
ruby hummel of east detroit got into the mustang love affair 
late but she got her drivers license late too she bought a used 
68 mustang when she got her license in 1973 at age 46 
it makes you feel young she said at a suburban detroit 
jeepeagle dealership where she and her husband were shopping for a 
new car they pulled up in a 66 light blue and white mustang a 
car she says she wont trade 
the nation is dotted with mustang clubs and mustang collectors 
about 75 percent of the members in the performance ford club of 
america are mustang owners said club chairman charles crites of 
ashville ohio 
mustang lovers praise what they call the simplicity of the early 
model promoting an exuberance and free spirit that captivated 
young consumers and made fords rivals rethink and redesign their 
own sporty models 
the original mustang unveiled when lee iacocca was president of 
ford had a base a price of 2368 and featured a 170cubicinch 
sixcylinder engine 
it could be fixed by a general novice person in the back 
yard in the early years crites said simplicity has gone out 
with cheap gas 
crites said hes owned about 15 mustangs over the years and has 
three in his collection of 25 cars his favorite mustang is the 
1969 mustang shelby gt 500 
like other mustang buyers crites is proud of how he found his 
pride and joy in 1970 i went in to a dealership to buy a 
truck he said i saw the mustang sitting there for 3700 i 
went back two weeks later and they dropped the price by about 
500 
crites drove it away that day 
he was one of hundreds of thousands who bought mustangs during 
the early years ford formally introduced the car on april 17 
1964 about five weeks after mustangs job 1 rolled out of fords 
dearborn plant 
some purists call the first editions 1964 models ford calls 
them 65s 
the firstyear sales projection of 100000 cars was passed in 
four months sales increased to its best year in 1966 when 549400 
mustangs were driven off ford dealership lots 
the second generation of mustangs called the mustang ii was 
introduced for the 1974 model year it was a smaller than the 73 
reflecting the need for better fuel efficiency during the oil 
crunch of the mid1970s 
mustang sales bottomed out in 1983 at about 117000 cars 
raising predictions that the car like an aging television sitcom 
had finally run out of gas but last year ford sold 170100 
mustangs 
the 1989 mustang which has a fourcylinder engine has a base 
price 9450 an optional beefedup 50liter engine capable of 223 
horsepower compared with 90 horsepower in the basic engine is a 
popular seller 
ford has said it plans to commemorate the mustang birthday this 
april 17 with a lowkey event at its dearborn headquarters but 
