<TEXT>
you can still get a 100 christian dior lace 
nightgown at bloomingdales swank manhattan store and buy a good 
offtherack suit from burdines in miami but their retailing 
parent has undergone a wrenching change in the year since a 
canadian developer took it over 
federated department stores inc which owns bloomies 
burdines and three other big department store chains is smaller 
leaner and more focused under its new boss robert campeau it has 
fewer stores fewer employees and a big mountain of debt 
it has survived predictions that it would become a financial 
ruin and retailing disaster 
but is it a better company today 
that remains to be seen says pamela stubing an analyst 
with moodys investor service inc only now she said is federated 
emerging from a tumultuous 12month transition 
