included a bidding war with rival retailer rh macy amp co inc the 
takeover cost campeau 67 billion 
he quickly sold four federated department store chains and its 
discount and specialty stores to help finance the deal 
campeau was accused of decimating a fine old retailer a charge 
hed heard before in december 1986 he bought allied stores corp 
for 34 billion and since then has sold 18 of its 24 store 
divisions 
campeau corp the umbrella for his retailing and real estate 
operations now owns nine department store companies jordan marsh 
the bon maas brothers and sterns from allied and bloomingdales 
burdines lazarus abraham amp straus and richsgoldsmiths from 
federated it also owns ralphs a southern california supermarket 
chain spun off from federated 
