federated should have done long before he came along 
when the developer first announced his offer for federated 
securities analysts accused thenchairman howard goldfeder of 
literally giving the store away by failing to streamline the 
company and make it more competitive 
campeau has cut annual operating costs at allied and federated 
by more than 350 million a year said 13d research services a 
yorktown heights ny firm that analyzes stocks and corporation 
finances 
campeau corp stock now trading in the teens could go as high 
as 66 a share this year 13d predicted in a report about his 
business 
while analysts agree that federated and allied needed 
streamlining they are concerned about its effect on the retailers 
its not yet known if they have done a good job in cutting 
down costs without destroying the stores said ms stubing of 
moodys 
but just the fact that the layoffs are behind campeaus 
employees has put the company on a better track said walter loeb 
an analyst with morgan stanley amp co 
everyones happier loeb said the employees are a more 
cohesive group 
some anxieties that prevailed a year ago apparently have not 
panned out many observers said the federated stores would become 
too centralized under campeau and lose their individuality and 
innovativeness 
loeb was reassured a year later saying each individual 
department store company is standing on its own two feet but 
with some direction from the home office 
campeau also was accused of buying the companies solely for 
their lucrative real estate and the entry that stores like 
bloomingdales would provide into new shopping malls 
real estate they said would take priority over good 
merchandising 
roddy doesnt deny that the companies properties was the 
principal draw for campeau as it has been for other 
developersturnedretailers such as edward debartolo jr and 
australias hooker corp 
you acquire shopping centers a lot easier if you acquire the 
company roddy said 
however he said campeau corp is now dependent on retailing 
for profit and the real estate end cannot survive without good 
performances from federated and allied 
the fact that there is growth in retail sales adds value to 
the underlying real estate values within retail roddy said 
with that in mind campeau has reworked federateds expansion 
plans to concentrate on its star bloomingdales division 
the company aims at opening three new bloomingdales a year 
said james zimmerman president of federated and allied campeau 
also is adding stores to other divisions and plans to expand or 
remodel more than half its 250 stores over the next five years 
zimmerman admitted that we didnt spend much of spring 88 
running the business because executives were busy cutting costs 
the company has made conservative projections for 1989 partly 
because of the sluggish consumer buying of the past two years 
zimmerman said campeau hoped for a sales increase of 4 percent 
consistent with industry projects at the start of 1989 
campeaus fourthquarter earnings havent been announced but 
some analysts expect an improvement from the third quarter when 
allied and federated lost a combined 535 million the high cost 
of paying the interest on takeoverrelated debt was partly to blame 
unlike most other big retailers federated and allied do not 
release their sales figures monthly making it difficult to assess 
their performance 
one industry analyst who asked not to be identified estimated 
that despite marginal sales growth for the year ended jan 31 
pretax earnings rose 5 percent at federated and 16 percent at 
allied thanks largely to cost cuts loeb the morgan stanley 
analyst said he expected campeau to adequately manage the heavy 
debt load it took on in acquiring federated and allied 
concerns about that debt wreaked havoc with its financing plans 
last fall 
campeau announced in september that federated and allied lost a 
combined 207 million during the second quarter when sales slowed 
the next month federateds planned 115 billion highyield bond 
sale had to be postponed and restructured 
published reports said buyers hesitated because of the 
retailers lackluster sales and losses but campeau said at the 
time the problem was uneasiness in the highyield bond market 
caused by the bidding war in the biggest debtfinanced takeover of 
all rjr nabisco inc 
roddy acknowledged that investors were concerned about campeaus 
debt but he expressed confidence the company can easily handle its 
interest payments 
the transition at federated has been rocky but the company says 
it is largely complete and analysts will be watching see if the 
takeover really was a good deal for robert campeau 
said ms stubing this year is going to be the really telling 
year 
